This paper presents a new variation of the pairing heap data structure, which is a type of self-adjusting heap. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the amortized time complexity of various operations, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.AL (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper involves some analysis of the structure, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm with improved time complexity, which could be relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
